The /optimizations/estimate API provides a response in the following format:

200 Success

EstimateOptimizationResponse Model - Response received when estimating the cost of an optimization.
estimate Estimate object
Response received when estimating the time to run an optimization job.
success boolean
Indicate if the API request was successful.
errors string Array
List of errors with the API call.
Example 
{
  "estimate": {
    "estimateId": "string",
    "time": 0,
    "balance": 0
  },
  "success": true,
  "errors": [
    "string"
  ]
}
Estimate Model - Response received when estimating the time to run an optimization job.
estimateId string
Estimate Id.
time integer
Estimated time in seconds to run the optimization job.
balance integer
The organization's QCC balance.
Example 
{
  "estimateId": "string",
  "time": 0,
  "balance": 0
}

401 Authentication Error

UnauthorizedError Model - Unauthorized response from the API. Key is missing, invalid, or timestamp is too old for hash.
www_authenticate string
Header
